This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a new class of policies for reinforcement learning and presents empirical results on their performance. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, the paper discusses the efficiency of algorithms, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The use of policies in computer vision tasks could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the properties of the policies, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
